title: Shares of several financial services companies are trading lower as equities sell off following recent rally. Stocks have rallied over the past week amid optimism towards the US economy reopening and investors have potentially taken some profits following run up. Investors are also awaiting Wednesday's Fed announcement.
Shares of several financial services companies are trading higher on continued optimism amid the reopening of the economy, which would increase consumer spending and economic activity.
